FT  01 AUG 92 / UK Company News: Mowat sells Norfolk Broads fleet for Pounds
4m
Mowat, the USM-quoted property and leisure group which is pulling out of
property development in the wake of Pounds 1.97m losses in the 15 months to
end-September, has announced the sale of the Potter Heigham boatyard and
fleet to Broad Tours, a private company, for Pounds 3.87m.
A cash payment of Pounds 1m is due on the completion date of October 31,
with a further Pounds 870,000 to be paid in instalments between March 31
1993 and September 30 1994. In addition there are two properties valued at
about Pounds 2m.
The proceeds will be used to reduce group borrowings.
